body: - There are three different levels of reviews for all files that hit Edgar: Full review
created_at: Targeted Review and No Review. Full review checks everything and  involves a team of 2 lawyers and 2 accountants.

body: - While there isn't much information on 40-F filing (the one TNT is using)
created_at: there are plenty of info on S-1 filing (standard filing for IPO). S-1 filing receives an AUTOMATIC full review
column3: and SEC Staff ALWAYS comes back with comments. I believe 40-F receives similar treatment

body: - The number of comments can range from 70-80 to a few. The fact that TNT only receives 2-3 comments is good.
- Median time to receive initial comments from SEC staff in 2017 was 26 days. Consider the impact of Covid and the amount of IPO in 2021
created_at: I think it is perfectly normal to receive comments on the 30th day for TNT's filing.
